// Workspace-scope formatter + file-mutation policy for .md files.
//
// HISTORY:
//   - 2026-05-03 commit 5a789c2: original four-key block disabled
//     editor.format* triggers for [markdown]. Resolved the format-on-*
//     firing pattern observed in Block 2 Sessions 1+2 (BLOCK_2_PLAN.md,
//     DESIGN.md, SETUP.md occurrences).
//   - 2026-05-03 mid-Session-3: regression on WORKFLOW.md during
//     Cursor's drop-before-commit step. Diagnostic: 1-byte off-by-one
//     across SHA-1 / line count / byte count, last 3 bytes ended
//     mid-content with no trailing newline. Signature of
//     `files.insertFinalNewline: true` firing on file open/save —
//     a `files.*` setting completely separate from the `editor.format*`
//     mechanism the original four-key block targeted.
//
// FIX:
//   The original four keys covered the formatter mechanism only. This
//   update adds five `files.*` and `editor.codeActionsOnSave` keys that
//   can mutate file content independently of the formatter:
//     - files.insertFinalNewline: false — was the directly-observed culprit.
//     - files.trimTrailingWhitespace: false — adjacent path; would explain
//       the "trailing blank line at 146" mutation we saw earlier.
//     - files.trimFinalNewlines: false — paired with insertFinalNewline.
//     - editor.codeActionsOnSave: {} — empty object disables any
//       extension-registered save action (markdownlint, etc.) running
//       at save time.
//     - editor.formatOnSaveMode: "file" — explicit; without this an
//       extension can register "modifications" mode and partial-format.
//
// All five are workspace-scope ([markdown] selector) only, so other
// file types (.js, .css, .html) keep their inherited defaults.
//
// REGRESSION CHECKLIST (if the formatter fires on .md again despite
// this file being present):
//   1. Verify this file is on disk and matches HEAD: git show HEAD:.vscode/settings.json
//   2. Reload Cursor window (Cmd+Shift+P → "Developer: Reload Window") —
//      settings.json changes don't always apply to already-open tabs.
//   3. Check user-scope settings: ~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/settings.json
//      may override workspace-scope for some keys.
//   4. Extension audit: Cmd+Shift+X, look for any markdown-related
//      extension. Disable at workspace scope via the extension's
//      gear-icon menu.
{
  "[markdown]": {
    "editor.formatOnSave": false,
    "editor.formatOnPaste": false,
    "editor.formatOnType": false,
    "editor.defaultFormatter": null,
    "editor.formatOnSaveMode": "file",
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {},
    "files.insertFinalNewline": false,
    "files.trimTrailingWhitespace": false,
    "files.trimFinalNewlines": false
  }
}
